{"lemma":"أَرْمِدَةٍ","slug":"أَرْمِدَةٍ","root":"ر.م.د","root_slug":"ر-م-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-م-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَماد","root":"رمد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16619"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ash, ashes"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From رَمِدَ (ramida, “to be inflamed”)."},"ipa":["/ra.maːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16619","headword_ar":"رَمَادٌ","root":"rmd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ashes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charcoal reduced to particles"},{"kind":"text","text":"T, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by being burnt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burnt coals that have become mixed with dust, and extinguished, and reduced to particles:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimodidaA='u","text_ar":"رِمْدِدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (S, M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromidaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْمِدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobiEaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْبِعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in some copies of the K, and in a copy of the S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromadaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْمَدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaEaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْبَعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in other copies of the K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iromidA='u","text_ar":"اـِرْمِدا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (so in two copies of the S, there said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_irobiEaA='u","text_ar":"اـِرْبِعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so in the M;) as some say; or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromidaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْمِدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAdN","text_ar":"رَمَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aromdapN","text_ar":"اَرْمدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iromidaA='u","text_ar":"اـِرْمِدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is mentioned on the authority of Kr, and which is [said to be] the only word of its measure, [though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_irobiEaA='u","text_ar":"اـِرْبِعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is mentioned by IHsh,] is a quasi-pl. n.: (M:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAdN","text_ar":"رَمَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a coll. gen. n.;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAdapN","text_ar":"رَمَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is its n. un., and as such] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [Hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN kaviyru ramaAdu Alqidori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ كَثِيرُ رَمَادُ القِدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has many ashes of the cooking-pot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is very hospitable; has many guests:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErD","text_ar":"عرض"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru Alr~amaAdi","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ الرَّمَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa EaZiymu Alr~amaAdi","text_ar":"هُوَ عَظِيمُ الرَّمَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he has many guests:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the ashes become much in quantity in consequence of cooking. (L, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufiYa Alr~amaAdu fiY wajohihi","text_ar":"سُفِىَ الرَّمَادُ فِى وَجْهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ashes were blown and scattered in his face"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his face became altered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='u Alr~amaAdi","text_ar":"مَا=ءُ الرَّمَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a term applied in the present day to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lixivium,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water infused with wood-ashes."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["M"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}